Elderfield Says ‘Breathing Down Necks’ of Banks on Arrears

-- B y   D a r a   D o y l e
-- 
2011-10-14T12:22:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-14/elderfield-says-breathing-down-necks-of-banks-on-arrears.html
Matthew Elderfield, the Irish
central bank’s head of financial regulation, said he’s
“breathing down the necks” of lenders on their handling of
mortgage arrears.  If banks “persist” in raising variable  interest rates , they
risk a cap on rates being introduced, he said in an interview
with Dublin-based RTE Radio aired today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dara Doyle at 
 ddoyle1@bloomberg.net  